  "response": "Here are some healthy ways to develop a more relaxed attitude:\n\n1. Focus on what you can control\n- Don't waste energy on things outside your influence\n\n2. Practice self-confidence\n- Build genuine self-esteem\n- Stop seeking constant approval from others\n\n3. Learn to set boundaries\n- Say no when necessary\n- Prioritize your own well-being\n\n4. Develop emotional resilience\n- Don't take things personally\n- Understand that other people's opinions don't define you\n\n5. Practice mindfulness\n- Stay present in the moment\n- Let go of unnecessary worries\n\n6. Choose your battles wisely\n- Not every situation requires an emotional response\n- Save your energy for what truly matters\n\n7. Cultivate a growth mindset\n- View challenges as opportunities\n- Learn from experiences instead of dwelling on them\n\n8. Reduce social media consumption\n- Limit comparison and external validation\n\n9. Practice self-care\n- Exercise\n- Meditate\n- Do things you enjoy\n\n10. Develop a sense of humor\n- Learn to laugh at yourself\n- Don't take life too seriously\n\nRemember, \"not giving a f***\" doesn't mean being callous or indifferent, but maintaining emotional balance and focusing on what truly matters to you.",
